article.headline: Arkansas 84, New Orleans 46
article.story:
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- Adrienne Bush scored a career high 18
points to lead Arkansas to an 84-46 win over New Orleans on
Wednesday.

Leslie Howard scored 15 points, Sheree Thompson added 12,
Dominique Washington 11 and Whitney Jones 10. Brittany Vaughn's 12
assists were a career high.

The Lady Razorbacks (7-4) scored 19 of 21 points over nine-plus
minutes, including a 17-0 run in 6:03 and was up 36-12 by halftime.

New Orleans (2-8) committed 20 turnovers in the opening period,
and the Privateers broke their scoreless drought with a layup with
5:45 left. In the first 10 minutes of the second half, New Orleans
doubled its point total and were only down by four.

Jada Frazier led with 12 points. Talisha Young added 10 points.
